articles.title: Banksy's NHS tribute sells for record $30 million as UK marks coronavirus lockdown anniversary - ABC News
articles.description: A Banksy pandemic painting smashes records and hauls in $30 million at auction with proceeds to go towards supporting the wellbeing of staff and patients at University Hospital in Southampton, where the painting first appeared.
articles.content:
A Banksy painting showing a young boy playing with a toy nurse as a superhero has sold for more than $30 million, setting an auction record for the elusive British street artist.
